post_text:
OGS 2020-2021 Family Survey (PLEASE SHARE)

Please click on the following link to fill out our Family Survey.
This survey will collect information to allow our administration and staff to plan for the current school year. Oak Grove plans to return to traditional school on the 11th. We will have a plan in case we need to close the district temporarily for distance learning as well as programs in place for virtual learning if parents are uncomfortable with traditional, in-class learning. By completing this survey, you will be giving us the information we need to help guide us in determining the best plan of action moving forward into this upcoming year. We want to do everything we can to keep all students safe while still providing a quality education and as much normalcy as possible. All surveys need to be turned in by Friday, 17th.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScv2RL6BQFzizScob1mLJaIDZb8jNYqWw5GDanbI_v6akZKTg/viewform?usp=pp_url

The date for the Oak Grove Middle school students 5th-8th FREE physical has been scheduled for Tuesday, July 14th 9:00-12:30.

5th-6th grade will begin at 9:00.
7th-8th at 11. If you have a sibling in 7th or 8th grade, they can come @ 9.

Please go to our website to get a copy of the required documents. The paperwork requires both parent and student signatures. You will not be able to get a physical without the signatures.

No playing outside on the playground or in the school. You will need to park in the back of the school and enter through the back gym door. Temperature checks will be taken before entering the building and students will be placed in the gym to wait their turn. Athletes ONLY , Parents can come in, but will be temp checked also. When the physical is over you must leave the buildings. Please practice social distancing at the school. If you have any questions please call the school and ask for Kelly. 918-352-2889

Thank you

Week 2A :

post_text:
A huge thank you is in order for Community Club members and everyone that has helped and continue to support Oak Grove. We are pleased to announce Oak Grove has a new sound system in the auditorium, including speakers!!!! It absolutely sounds wonderful and should be in working order prior to the next Rise and Shine on Oct 31st and for many, many years to come!!! I am not suppose to mention anyone by name so I will not, but their names rhyme with Marrah Sattox and Ressika Joss. They are not the only ones that have helped, but they did head the project and spent many hours finding the best fit for Oak Grove. Can't wait for all to hear and if you are not a part of the Community Club, check them out and get involved, they are doing some great things!!!

From everyone at Oak Grove.

post_text: Mr. Aven enjoyed our time at the Cushing Lake on Friday!
text: Mr. Aven enjoyed our time at the Cushing Lake on Friday!

post_text: The 6th and 7th grade geography classes spent the afternoon with Cushing City Manager Terry Brannon, James Landis, and Emily Long. Terry Brannon provided lunch. We spent time talking about the history of the Cushing Lake, the damage to the lake, the environment, sources of Cushing water, and careers in the environmental field. Mr. Brannon took our OGS students to the Cushing Lake to discuss those things as well. We spent time discussing the damage to the lake. We are very thankful for the time Mr. Brannon spent with our students. We had an amazing afternoon.
